name: flutter_settings
desc:
A package to set custom values in Shared Preferrences in a screen with
provided input fields.

name: ChangePasswordConfig
desc: Configuration to enable to user to change his password in the profilescreen.

name: enablePasswordChange
desc: Enables the textfields for the user to provide a new password.

name: fieldRequiredErrorText
desc: Error text to be shown when either of the textfields is empty.

name: notEqualErrorText
desc:
Error text to be shown when the second password isn't equal
to the first password.

name: saveButtonBuilder
desc: Ability to override the standard 'save password' button.

name: title
desc: Text for the title above the textfields.

name: titleStyle
desc: Textstyle of the title.

name: underTitle
desc: Text for the undertitle just above the textfields.

name: underTitleStyle
desc: Textstyle for the undertitle

name: content
desc:
This is an optional param. You should either set content or other params
but not both. If content is not null the content is shown instead of the
ControlType.

name: description
desc: The description is shown next to the setting

name: formatInputs
desc: Input formatters to limit input.

name: isRequired
desc: Specify if the field is required when shown on registration pages

name: key
desc: The key is used to store the value in the shared preferences

name: keyboardType
desc: The keyboardType (used for textFields)

name: onChange
desc: This method is invoked everytime the user changes the setting

name: prefixIcon
desc: The Widget that is shown on the left side of the input.

name: settings
desc:
The settings is a List containing the Controls that are shown grouped
together inside a Container. The settings should only be used if the
ControlType is Group.

name: title
desc: The title is shown above the Control

name: type
desc: The type is the type of Control. To see all the options see ControlType.

name: validator
desc:
Fields can be validated by one or multiple validators with custom error
messages. (used for textFields)

name: value
desc:
The value is the defaultvalue along with the items or options depending on
whether the ControlType requires items or options to be given. If the
ControlType is a bool the value should also be a bool. If the ControlsType
is a DropDown the value should be a MapR containing the int selected and
the items in the form of a List with Strings. If the ControlType is a
Radio the value should be a Map containing int selected and List
options. If the ControlType is range the Map should contain max, min and
selected. All three are doubles.

name: ControlType
desc:
The settings are saved to shared preferences. Use the key you set to extract
the value of the settings.

name: ProfilePage
desc:
The ProfilePage widget is able to show the data of a user. By default the
user is able to change this data. The widget has a couple of
parameters listed below:

name: avatarBackgroundColor
desc: The background color of the avatar when no image is available.

name: bottomActionText
desc:
Sets the text for the InkWell at the bottom of the profile page.
The InkWell is disabled when null.

name: changePasswordConfig
desc: Configuration to give the user the option to change his/her password.

name: createState
desc: Creates the mutable state for this widget at a given location in the tree.

name: customAvatar
desc: The way to override the standard avatar is needed.

name: extraWidgets
desc:
The map of extra widgets that might want to be added like empty
SizedBoxes for styling.

name: formKey
desc: Use the form key to save on any custom callback

name: itemBuilder
desc: Itembuilder is used the build each field in the user.

name: itemBuilderOptions
desc: Used to set settings of each field in user.

name: prioritizedItems
desc:
Map keys of items that should be shown first before the default
items and the rest of the items.

name: service
desc: The service the determine what should happen when the user takes action.

name: showAvatar
desc: Whether to show the users avatar.

name: showDefaultItems
desc: Shows textfields for firstname and lastname if is set to true

name: showItems
desc:
Whether you want to show the input fields, sometimes you just want
to edit the avatar.

name: style
desc: Style to set some general styling parameters fot the whole page.

name: user
desc: User containing all the user data.

name: wrapItemsBuilder
desc: Customize the parent widget for all fields

name: wrapViewOptions
desc: Edit the direction and spacing between every item

name: ProfileService
desc:
ProfileService can be extended and set for the profilePage.
The following method can be overriden.

name: ProfileStyle
desc:
ProfielStyle is used to set a couple of style paramaters for the
whole profile page.

desc: AvatarStyle can be used to set some avatar styling parameters.

name: betweenDefaultItemPadding
desc: BetweenDefaultItemPadding sets the

name: bottomActionTextStyle
desc: Bottom action text style

name: pagePadding
desc:
PagePadding can be set to determine the padding of the whole page
againt the profile page parent.

name: RadioItem
desc: Creates an item for a radio menu.

name: onTap
desc: Called when the dropdown menu item is tapped.

name: value
desc: The value to return if the user selects this menu item.

name: diameterRatio
desc:
A ratio between the diameter of the cylinder and the viewport's size in
the main axis.

name: highlightWidget
desc:
Override the standard highlight widget. (Grey container which is placed
behind the selected item).

name: itemHeight
desc:
Height of each item in the scrollwheel. Chaging this changes the height
of the widget.

name: magnification
desc: The zoomed-in rate of the magnifier, if it is used.

name: numberOfVisibleItems
desc:
Amount of visible items in the scroll wheel. Changing this changes the
height of the widget.

name: offAxisFraction
desc:
How much the wheel is horizontally off-center, as a fraction of its width.
This property creates the visual effect of looking at a vertical wheel
from its side where its vanishing points at the edge curves to one side
instead of looking at the wheel head-on.

name: overAndUnderCenterOpacity
desc:
The opacity value that will be applied to the wheel that appears below
and above the magnifier.

name: perspective
desc:
Size of each child in the main axis. Must not be null and
must be positive.

name: renderChildrenOutsideViewport
desc: Whether to paint children inside the viewport only.

name: scrollItemBuilder
desc: Ability to provide your own builder for the scroll items

name: scrollItemTextStyle
desc:
Textstyle of the scroll items. Will be overridden if the
scrollItemBuilder is set.

name: squeeze
desc: The angular compactness of the children on the wheel.

name: useMagnifier
desc: Whether to use the magnifier for the center item of the wheel.
